		"Name": "Blue Shield Particle Field Dampener",
		"Details": "The Blue Shield Particle Field Dampener, or BSPFD for short, is an experimental Federated Suns system that was designed to dramatically reduce incoming damage from PPC-type weapons. In this, it was highly successful but in order to achieve such success the system developed a number of other notable flaws. For one, it was prone to failure due to accumulated dust and battlefield detritus jamming the components over time. For another, the attached linkages across the mech's body were highly charged and liked to explode when damaged by weapons fire. Finally, the Blue Shield had a bad habit of destroying itself when it failed, making it highly expensive to maintain on active combat units. With all of these drawbacks, the New Avalon Institute of Science eventually shelved the project, with it only appearing sporadically on the game world of Solaris VII.",
